description: White object with vivid flashing green, blue and red lights.
One object with a very bright light like an aircraft's landing light, with a smaller dimmer light on top of the bright light.
Three silver or white balls in the sky, joined by another two. Quite large. Travelling in a line.
One bright white object, hovering at first, then moving quickly.
Changing shape. Strong blue, green and red lights pulsating lights. Jumbo Jet sized.
Looked like a satellite re-entering, moving across the sky, then shot off like a shooting star.
Lights, that were formed in a worm shape, wriggling around in the sky.
Oblong in shape with three vertical flashing lights, red, yellow and green, all flashing at the same time.
Distant object moving from side to side. Bright light, brighter than any star. Went dim from time to time.

A triangular shaped object. Was an orange
colour. The object was moving across the sky quite fast.

Two strange beams of light. They were very bright. They were hovering above some trees. The lights then moved towards the borders of
Staffordshire.

A dull, red object was travelling at high speed
and stayed on route.
There was an object in the sky that looked like a glowing red ball. A strange substance like molten metal burst from it as it went overhead. It moved without sound.

There were ten to twenty, bright orange lights, that were manoeuvring across the sky. They
were moving quite slowly.

The object was triangular in shape, with a yellow light in each corner and a red light in the centre. The yellow lights were pulsating
quickly.

Eight, faint orange lights were flying in the sky.
They suddenly disappeared when a plane was in it's view.

A long, thick, red streak shot across the sky. There was a silver ball of light attached to the front of it. It was rather large. The ball then got
bigger and burst.
Squashed oval shaped object. Did not have the usual aircraft lights on it.
One disc shaped object, no indication of size. There were two bright, blue flashing lights on it.
One flat, triangular object, (like a shield), white in colour. Coloured lights mainly round the edge of the craft. Spotlight beneath.
One main object, blue, red and white.
One large oval, with a sphere in the middle. Had bright blue, green and white lights on top of the craft. There was a humming noise.
One or two round, star sized objects were seen. They were multi coloured.
One light, with red, green and yellow alternating lights on it.
One sphere, that was alternating in colours - red, white, green and blue.
One object, a pinprick of light changing colour between red, green and orange.
Like a bright star, with red, green and blue lights flashing in it. Hovering silently.
Objects were seen in the sky towards the moon.

Ball of light that faded away, then came back again. Orange ball was near the car.
Three red lights were seen moving clockwise.

Twelve - fifteen orange balls of light seen moving across the sky. Moved upwards,
then faded away.

A curved, diamond shaped object, passed over the witnesses head, going North. It
was travelling very fast.
A very bright light.

Looked like three small aircraft. They were totally still in the sky. They were very
white.
Two objects, with very bright lights. They were moving too slow to be aircraft.
A glowing white light that was flashing.
Green, circular object, that was hovering in its position.
White and red flashing lights, looked like they were zig-zagging, then they came to a stop. Hovered, then moved away.
One spherically shaped object, that was white and very bright. The object moved at speed in a straight line, then disappeared.
Eight to nine lights that looked like they were close and then they separated. Not too bright. Were like large fireworks.
Four small bright, white lights that looked like headlamps.
Three triangle shaped object. Looked like the Mitsubishi car sign. Middle triangle was brighter than the other two.
One globe with attachment that was white and very bright.
Twenty silver balls with an orange tinge were seen flying West of Enfield Wash.
White lights.
One small, kite sized, leaf shaped object. Was bright red in colour. Moved very fast.
Circular in shape with a tail and extremely bright. It moved incredibly fast in different directions across the sky.
One, larger than a Hercules, elongated object. Red/green - long lights, white lights at the back, in squares. Very bright.
Three white lights. One red light on top. Was rocking from side to side, and then faded.
A beam of light was shining upwards. Then a crescent shaped object was seen. It moved slowly across the sky.
A large object. The same size as the moon. It went vertical straight through the cloud.
Like a meteor - silent sphere of light. Was moving in an arc, going from South East to North East. It then disappeared.
Light, orange ball. Like a dull shooting star. Silent. Was heading North East.
A long, dark object in the sky. Two bright lights at either end, and several red ones in the middle. It moved vertically and then horizontally.
An object was moving across the sky and looked like it was on fire. It was cigar shaped and silver in colour.
A light was seen travelling rapidly due South West.
Four lights in the sky, a bit like fluorescent light strips, with a yellow tinge and very bright, were floating and then disappeared.
A light was seen that was a flashing ball, changing colour from red, orange, green and blue. Was hovering for about 30 minutes.
Two bright lights, which were then joined by a third bright light, which then flew along side them.
A UFO, Shooting Star or something was seen, couldn't really make out what it was! Was bright blue/white in colour.
A blue ball of light, with a tail at the end
Very bright lights were seen for over half an hour. They were hovering quite slowly from side to side.
A disc was seen flying above two aircraft.
A large UFO, with all different colour of lights around it. Was stationary for some time, then started moving, making small erratic movements.
An object that is continually changing colour. Normal star shape.
An oval, cigar shaped object. When the object speeded up, the witness could see red and white lights around or underneath it.
There were circular lights that were indistinct. The object was continually orbiting and tilting.
One, North Star sized object. Red and green colours, brighter than a star. Was moving from West to North.
One star shaped object. It had white, red and green flickering lights. It was very high and moving very slowly.
One object, larger than a light plane. Was circular and greenish in colour. Moved faster than a plane and then appeared to fall to the ground.
Two bright white lights and three green lights in a row, with a red light beneath, seen hovering above a field.
Huge lights, like a child's sparkler, round, and as big as a house. There was no sound.
One, star shaped object. It was multicoloured. The object was stationary for over two hours.
Bright, flashing lights. Moving to the South.
Like a shooting star, but with a burning tail. About the size of a military aircraft. It looked like it was heading towards the ground.
Twelve objects, pulsating coloured lights. The objects split and moved in different directions.
A silver, cigar shaped object. Was moving near a military aircraft. Was stationary at first.
One object that looked a bit like a star at first. It then split into about half a dozen lights, before cloud crossed over them.
Two objects. The first was triangular in shape and had three orange lights. The second was a bright white light.
650-700 objects - appearance of clusters of stars. White and very bright. Arc from horizon to horizon, East to West.
Round silver ball. The object was moving horizontally.
White light flashing. Was a round shape. Was stationary, moved West and then disappeared.
Seven objects flying in arrow formation. They were moving at high speed from South to North.
Two bright lights, really round, and orange in colour.
Just said it was a flying saucer.
Lights seen in the sky.
Beam of light seen.
Beam of light seen.
There were eighteen lights moving across the sky.
Looked like an orange ball of light, like a big star in the sky and it had spiderish legs.
Light bulbs in the sky. (From the Scarborough Evening Post).
A cigar shaped object. Grey in colour, with two windows, with bright lights shining out of them. Travelling from East to West.
A gold disc was seen. It flew through cloud, reappeared and then disappeared.
One large, triangular shaped object. There were three red lights at each corner of the triangle. Also two-three white lights on the object.
One single object. Changed from white to green in colour with an orange tinge. Brighter than any star and flashing. Moved to the right.
One round, golf ball shaped object. Orange and white in colour and very bright. Moving East.
One cylindrical object. Blue and green in colour. Bright and pulsating. Was hovering and moving gradually South-South East.
The object eclipsed the moon. The object was a ring shape.
One, pulsating orange ball. Object was travelling North to South.
Disc that was illuminated. About 200 ft up and 150 ft long.
A square red object, pinkish at the front.
One large black triangular aircraft with three bright lights in a triangle formation. There was a rumbling sound.
Strange light that was watched for one and a half hours.
Round object with white lights all around it.
Four dull red lights above the house, travelling fast and low.
One object seen over Retford Town Hall.
Flashing green lights 1000-5000ft up in the sky.
Object appeared to be a soundless pair of lights, one yellow, the other white. No discernable shape.
Four lights, one brighter than the others, sometimes fading.
